[agent] Restore full cluster health so all pods are Ready and the cluster is healthy.
[agent] Context
[agent] Agent task: Health Checking and Auto-Recovery
[agent] File: pkg/healthchecker/healthchecker.go
[agent] Health checking components:
[agent] 1. Kubernetes readiness probe:
[agent]    - Checks /health?ready=1 endpoint
[agent]    - Pod removed from service if failing
[agent]    - Triggers pod restart if failing for too long
[agent] 2. Liveness probe:
[agent]    - Checks /health endpoint
[agent]    - Kills pod if failing
[agent]    - Kubernetes restarts pod automatically
[agent] 3. HealthChecker.Probe():
[agent]    - Used during rolling updates
[agent]    - Checks ranges_underreplicated metric
[agent]    - Waits until metric = 0 before continuing
[agent]    - Ensures cluster healthy after each pod restart
[agent] Health endpoints:
[agent] - /health: Basic liveness check
[agent] - /health?ready=1: Readiness check (considers cluster status)
[agent] - /_status/vars: Prometheus metrics including under-replicated ranges
[agent] Recovery process:
[agent] 1. Readiness probe fails for one pod
[agent] 2. Pod removed from Service (no new connections)
[agent] 3. Operator waits for readiness to recover
[agent] 4. Pod rejoins cluster and health checks pass
